users : track owner / track reviewer / admin / runner
        track owner can add tasks and exercises which can be re ordered
        track owner assigns the exercise to the possible reviewers 
        reviewer can accept or reject the exercise
        runner can be assigned tracks and mark each task as started and finished
        runners submit solution for review
admin : add track / add user / assign track owners
tracks : name / 

------
users : id, name,email, admin(boolean)
tracks : track_id, name, track_owner_id
tasks : task_id, track_id, name, description

tracks_runner_reviewer : id,track_id, user_id, started_on, track_reviewer_id, finished_on 

tasks_runners : user_id, task_id, started/finished, reviewer_id, rejected/accepted


note: to reduce the table columns , we can think of removing the fields runners and reviewer and make a separate table for that or just remove the entries and try to find people who are runners currently using taks_runners table and similarly for reviewers.

mysql> create table users ( 
    -> id int auto_increment primary key,
    -> name varchar(20) not null,
    -> admin boolean not null default '0');
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.37 sec)

mysql> alter table users add email varchar(20) not null after name;
Query OK, 6 rows affected (0.38 sec)
Records: 6  Duplicates: 0  Warnings: 0

